<br>
So… what can I complain about here?  <br>
Our fists and MA weapons have very low crit bonuses compared to the weapons other classes use. <br>
From Hacker’s quest database:<br>
200 MA skill Fist damage= 20-50(30)<br>
QL50 Acroblade damage=  26-29(33) <br>
This acroblade requires 256 MA skill and 171 piercing<br>
Both are fists and the acroblade are pretty fast<br>
<br>
Compare to:<br>
QL50 Gripo-Com AKR 1K21 damage = 5-82(254)<br>
The Gripo requires 219 rifle skill and is FASTER than our fists<br>
QL48 Over-Tuned Nova Flow - Mk IV damage = 1-92(108)<br>
The nova requires 190 Assault rifle and 126 LR_energy and is slightly slower than our fists<br>
I won’t even list Krutts and Vektors here because their crit damage is obscene. These comparisons are between weapons using similar skill requirements, but we know that weapon using classes get temporary buff to wield higher level weapons and therefore enjoy even larger crit bonuses. <br>
<br>
Conclusion: Other classes can benefit MUCH more from our crit buffs than we can. If the critical hit is a defining attribute of MAs why are our weapons have such low crit bonuses?<br>
<br>
<br>
