Vandame <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=marwyn>Marwyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#660000>(12/11/01 7:49:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1472.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> MAs vs ANYONE crits</span><hr size=1> Go to Mort, there make nice team with any other professions, go to factory and buff all members with VS. What happen ? Doctor will have higher damage output than you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  (dont want talk about any other SUPERCRITs weapons users) Doc can crit with his nice shotgun (or what the hell Docs using) for 2k+ on level ~100 and he crit with VS 2 times from 5 shots ! if you have team 1 doc + 3 Sold + 1 NT + 1 MA you are able solo everything, but MA is there only exp sucker and crit buff machine <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucson777.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cson777</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#660000>(12/11/01 8:29:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1472.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MAs vs ANYONE crits</span><hr size=1> Yeah, Whygirl2 has a nice shotgun; she's a lvl 100+ doc with a QL 80 shotgun. She's up to date on all her healing nanos, and she packs a punch. And to think, I rerolled an MA because missions were taking too long with a doc. I should have just stuck with the doc. Everyone except dual pistol wielding adventureres outdamage MAs. It's pathetic, but I just upgraded to Greater Healing which is 350-800 heal. I teamed with soldiers, agents, and a meta; and we were able to solo borgs, even brigs.<br>
<br>
I have one good thing to say about MAs. We have green evades. At lvl 102 with my evades maxed and buffed, I don't get critted as often as some of the other classes.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uknuklesninefingers.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Knukles Ninefingers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#660000>(12/11/01 1:02:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1472.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Of course</span><hr size=1> Of course your crit buff benefits others more than you, but that's why you have it instead of them. I was thinking just the other day after getting Sub G cast on my soldier, &quot;boy, if soldiers had Sub G, they would be unstoppable&quot; well, that's why they dont have it. If Sub G did as much for an MA as it did for a weapon user, then it would be an imbalance. As far as shotguns go, no profession can increase shotgun skill more than 4 points per level(soldiers and traders are best, but still only light blue 4pts/level) and there is no shotgun buff beyond expertise so they have to have some advantage.<br>
<br>
Plankk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/unutbar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NutBar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>They call me Bruce.</span><br>  Posts: 234<br> <font color=#660000>(12/11/01 1:23:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1472.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://files.sobservers.com/New%20Files/nut/scary2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Of course</span><hr size=1> Shotguns are MUCH earier to over equip than other weapon such as assault rifles and rifles because Vektors require only the shotgun skill, no extra skills such as burst, or full auto.<br>
<br>
a level 20ish trader can buff their shotgun skill by:<br>
+20 general nano<br>
+67 QL50 implants (could go higher with some work)<br>
+40 Deprive skills<br>
+34 ransack skills<br>
+80 Wrangle<br>
-----------------<br>
+241 total<br>
<br>
They get around 5 points of shotgun per level (4+1 from STR/AGI)<br>
<br>
So at level 20 they can get up to ~341 shotgun skill and easily use a <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://ao.hackersquest.org/show.php3?id=124260&amp;item=1">QL 70 Vektor ND LIZARD shotgun</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying that MA should have the best criticals.  I'm pointing out that we have the worst criticals. This turn us into a support character at higher levels.<br>
<br>
Side note- why do shotguns and beams have such high critical hits?  I think of a critical hit as something precise, like an aimed shot from a rifle or a well placed thrust from an acroblade. <br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucson777.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cson777</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#660000>(12/11/01 1:41:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1472.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Of course</span><hr size=1> I disagree. Our crit buffs are meant to be shared. Why would Funcom give MA a nano line that would benefit another class more than itself? Why not make MA crit buffs self-only, like the soldier's MK? That's what Funcom would have done if they thought the crit buffs would make another class overpowering (Like the Traders comp literacy buffs which enbled lvl 10 players put on 5-slot belts). I personally think that Funcom didn't throughly think out the minimum damage of fists.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uknuklesninefingers.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Knukles Ninefingers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#660000>(12/11/01 3:55:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1472.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> crit buff</span><hr size=1> Ok, obviously I was misunderstood, when I said you got it and it benefits others more than you I meant that it was the MA's contribution to a group. I really dont understand why you are upset at this nano, its got to be one of the best nanos in the game. The fact that fists dont have a high critical and have bad stats is most likely due to the fact that fists are free and always available. Sure a trader can overequip a Vektor, I had a 78 trader with a Ql 117 vektor, awesome crits, but the gun was slow and it could still hit for 15 damage on occasion. But you know what? chances are I'd STILL be using that same vektor at level 100 or more because the availability of QL125+ weapons (especially on RK2) is very rare and expensive, fists are free and you always get an upgrade, funcom had to take this into consideration when assigning fists. I personally think an MMRPG shoots themselves in the foot when they have an unarmed class/profession, it its extremely hard to balance it out in fairness. At level 150, you're guranteed to have QL150 fist damage, that is one trade off to the class, you can never really over equip, but you'll never be underequipped either, now Im not against any class getting an upgrade(I think all professions could use a boost in damage output), but in fairness they would need to make QL 200 weapons available in shops. I remember using the newbie solder weapon til level 9 (when I got my first nova flow). I've played a 50 MA, 78 Trader, 77 Soldier so I don't speak from lack of experience, but I can tell you this, both the soldier and MA could outdamage the trader even with a massively equipped vektor and both had more hps. <br>
<br>
Cson777, MAs get the controlled destruction, self only short duration offensive buff, enforcers get challenger and soldiers get the shield. Sure the shield is better than either the challenger or controlled destruction nanos, but honestly I'd trade the shield for healing any day.<br>
<br>
This is some great discussion btw.<br>
<br>
Tone <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucson777.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cson777</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#660000>(12/11/01 4:36:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1472.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: crit buff</span><hr size=1> Knukles, I'm not attacking you. In fact I agree with you on almost everything. We can actually &quot;overequip&quot; by implanting. For example, I put on a full set of QL 125 implants at around lvl 65 (legitimate w/o treatment stacking). Back then, I was bragging about soloing 80% missions, getting QL 110 armor that I can actually use, killing everything in the mission in under an hour. Now, at lvl 102, I have the same old implants, and I can't find implants QL 125+ because I can't do anything more than 50% missions. <br>
<br>
And the controlled destruction line, in my and other MAs opinion, are pretty much useless. Whereas the Soldier's MK is his bread and butter. <br>
<br>
As for heals, that's about the best thing about the MAs (and our crit line). I actually had a doctor just prior to the MA. I liked him a lot, but fights took too long. Sure, a doc can continuously heal himself, but he does so little damage, that it takes forever.<br>
<br>
My MA was great. Good damage plus the ability to heal himself. But if you ever get your MA to around lvl 80 or so, I think you'll understand what most of the MAs on the board are talking about. Sure I can chain heal over and over again, but at lvl 102, I'm constantly doing 109 damage with exceptional crits and brawls. And Yellow MOBs at my level have something like 10k life. And a Green Anun Tearer hits for 150, but twice as fast, and has three times the HPs. Even if I chain heal (350-800 each, 1500+ nano pool). I barely survive. I have to zone at least three times for a yellow Greater Anun.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucson777.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cson777</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#660000>(12/11/01 4:41:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1472.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: crit buff</span><hr size=1> BTW, I'm not upset at our crit line, and I hope Funcom doesn't make it self-only. Our crit line is about the only reason a group wants MAs. I actually rerolled an MA because I was in Tir County fighting Buzzsaws, I saw this MA in my group doing consistent high damage, while my pistols were doing 15 or so. And he was healing. We had a soldiers and fixers as well, but their damage wasn't nearly as consistent or high as the MA's. But at higher levels, that seems to change. If I team with soldiers and traders, I know it's going to be a quick kill. If I team with three other MAs, it's a long battle. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/unutbar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NutBar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>They call me Bruce.</span><br>  Posts: 235<br> <font color=#660000>(12/11/01 6:34:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1472.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://files.sobservers.com/New%20Files/nut/scary2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nano discussion #3: Critical hit buffs</span><hr size=1> It's true that we do just fine until we hit the dreaded title max wall at level 82.  From then on we are &quot;underequipped&quot; with our fists because we will still be using the same level 82 fists when we are level 99, then we can start adding 5 points per level again, always 18 levels behind.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uautumndawnfire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Autumn Dawnfire</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.melanierawn.com/images/bunnie.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#660000>(12/15/01 6:08:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1472.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> interesting</span><hr size=1>  A few points:  <br>
I think we have low crit's on the Fists specifically because of the fact we can self crit buff, personally i think the chances are way to low, and i have a sneaking susupicion that there is a base chance to crit for each profession,  I say that because back in the early days of the game a solider friend that was keeping up a brawl skill consistantly posted higher max brawls then I ever did with the solider having a lower skill ( which was annoying as hell ).  Personally if that is the case I'd like to have the same chance to crit as any other melee class.<br>
<br>
